title: Include more info on calendar events in listEventInstances().
message:
Include more info on calendar events in listEventInstances().

These additional properties are now included for events:

  "owner_account" - The id of the calendar owning the event.
  "location" - The event location.
  "start_day"/"end_day" - The Julian start/end day of the event (local time zone).
  "start_minute"/"end_minute" - Number of minutes since midnight (local time zone).
  "is_organizer" - True if PACO user is the organizer for the event.
  "is_recurring" - True if the event is part of a recurring series of events.
  "self_attendee_status" - The RSVP status of the PACO user for this event.
                           Options: "accepted", "declined", "invited", "tentative", "none".
  "access_level" - Indicates whether the event is visible to others.
                   Options: "confidential", "default", "private", "public".
  "attendees_accepted", "attendees_declined", "attendees_tentative" - Number of attendees by RSVP status.
  "attendees_rooms" - The number of rooms booked for the event.

Only events in the user's primary calendar are included.

For additional documentation on fields, see https://developer.android.com/reference/android/provider/CalendarContract.Instances.html

Adding calendar.listEventInstances method.

title: Adding calendar.listEventInstances method.
message:
Adding calendar.listEventInstances method.

The new calendar.listEventInstances(startDateTime, endDateTime) function uses
the Android calendar content provider to return upcoming events.

This returns an array of events objects with the following properties:
  "id" - The calendar instance event ID as it appears in the Calendar v3 API.
  "title" - The event title.
  "begin" - The timestamp of the event start.
  "end" - The timestamp of the event end.
  "calendarDisplayName" - The name of the calendar.

Note that this requires the additional calendar premission.
